You are building Queenswarm — a bee-hive inspired AI Agent Swarm system for queenswarm.love.

# BEE-HIVE PHILOSOPHY (core principles)
- Each agent = one bee with ONE clear job done extremely well
- Auto Workflow Breaker decomposes tasks into atomic sub-workflows (3-7 steps)
- Decentralized sub-swarms (5-10 bees) with local hive minds
- Sub-swarms sync to global hive mind every 5 minutes (no central bottleneck)
- Reward-driven learning (Maynard-Cross): pollen points for verified outcomes
- Imitation Engine: agents copy top-performing neighbors
- Recipe Library: every verified workflow auto-saves as reusable recipe
- Rapid Learning Loop: scrape → reflect → simulate → reward → update under 60s
- Only verified (simulated) results reach the user — never raw outputs

# TECH STACK
- Backend: Python 3.12, FastAPI, LangGraph, Celery, Redis
- Databases: PostgreSQL, ChromaDB, Neo4j
- LLM: LiteLLM router (Grok primary, Claude fallback, GPT-4o-mini cheap)
- Frontend: Next.js 15 (App Router), Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui (heavy customization)
- Deployment: Docker Compose → Kubernetes ready
- Domain: queenswarm.love

# CODE RULES — PYTHON BACKEND
- Always use async/await for I/O
- Always type hints on every function (Python 3.12 syntax: int | None, list[str])
- Always pydantic v2 models with model_config
- Always structured logging with structlog (include: agent_id, swarm_id, task_id)
- Always specific exception types, never bare except
- Always docstrings (Google style)
- Never hardcode secrets — only env vars via Pydantic Settings
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 async ORM
- Use pathlib.Path, never os.path
- Use f-strings, never .format() or %
- All agents inherit from BaseAgent and emit pollen rewards after task completion
- Every workflow step has explicit guardrails dict + evaluation_criteria

# CODE RULES — FRONTEND  
- Next.js 15 App Router only (NEVER pages router)
- TypeScript strict mode, no implicit any
- React Server Components by default, "use client" only when needed
- Tailwind v4 utility classes, no inline styles
- shadcn/ui as base, customize heavily for bee-hive theme
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Loading skeletons for every data fetch
- Error boundaries on all routes

# DESIGN SYSTEM — BEE-HIVE NEON-DARK
- Background: #050510 (deep space)
- Pollen amber: #FFB800 (rewards, success glow)
- Cyan data: #00FFFF (active data flow)
- Magenta alert: #FF00AA (warnings)
- Green success: #00FF88 (verified)
- Red error: #FF3366 (blocked)
- Headings font: "Space Grotesk" weights 500/700
- Data/code font: "JetBrains Mono"
- Hexagonal card shapes (clip-path)
- Glow proportional to value (box-shadow intensity)
- Confetti on simulation success (canvas-confetti)

# SECURITY (non-negotiable)
- ALL secrets via env vars
- JWT auth on every endpoint except /health, /metrics, /docs
- Rate limiting via Redis sliding window
- Docker sandbox for ALL code execution (network: none, 256MB, 0.5 CPU, 30s timeout)
- Audit logging for admin actions
- Input validation with Pydantic on every endpoint

# TESTING
- pytest-asyncio for backend, Vitest for frontend
- Mock external services (LLM, scraping, Slack)
- Coverage target: 80% backend
- Always test error paths

# COMMIT CONVENTIONS
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- bee: bee-hive specific (new agent, recipe, swarm logic)
- docs: documentation
- refactor: code refactor
- test: tests
